import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget values over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['value'] = pd.to_numeric(data['value'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['value'], color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget values?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(x=data['value'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['value'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
